cave:
    play sound click
    choice:
        "Parsnip the Sheep is somewhere in the woods. Probably. Maybe."
        "[Run around the woods going <span class='writtenText'>'pspspspspspsps'</span>] <span class='prompt'>[[-1 ACTION]]</span>" if (>= $stats.actions.value 1):
            play sound spendAction
            set data.game_map.inMap false
            add_stat actions -1
            set_button button_cave false
            run transition_black woods_one
            clear_dialog
        "<span class='prompt'>[[BACK]]</span>":
            jump game_map
    
    play ambient amb_forest 1
    "If Parsnip is anywhere, it's the woods. All roads lead to them, eventually."
    clear_dialog
    if $data.cryptids.cryptidsDone:
        if $data.cryptids.scared:
            talk nasty talk "Let's just keep an look out in case that fucking beastie comes for us again, okay girls."
            talk lovely talk "One eye always behind our back, quite right, Nasty Girl! Orb, keep a look out."
            talk orb talk "Sigh."
    jump cave_woods_menu

cave_woods_menu:
    clear_dialog
    if (&& $data.cave.air $data.cave.branch $data.cave.tree $data.cave.scrungler $data.cave.song $data.cave.shout $data.cave.orb):
        choice:
            "You wander, basically aimlessly through the woods for some time before you stumble upon it: a cave. A cave that is, curiously, locked off by a metal gate."
            "[Approach the cave]":
                jump cave_cave
    else:
        choice:
            "The woods are quiet. The woods are full of bird song and the rustling of trees. The woods are dirty. The woods are nice. The woods are calm. The woods are scary. The wood is a million identical trees, a trillion unique leaves. The woods are a place of contrasts."
            "[Smell the air]":
                set data.cave.air true
                choice:
                    "The air smells clean. Cleaner than the air on Daffodil lane, and far cleaner than the air in Bluehills. It smells of wet, but in a good way."
                    "Sigh. This is nice. [Do a gay little smile and reflect on the glory of nature then get a little bit sad for some reason]":
                        talk lovely talk "Cheer up, mon amie."
                        clear_dialog
                        talk orb talk "I'm sad too. Nature is so beautiful... so transient..."
                        talk orb talk "None of this will survive forever. None of it at all..."
                        talk orb talk "This world teeters on the edge of so many armageddons. There was never any hope for it and its creatures..."
                        talk orb talk "I wish I could see more of it. In person, I mean..."
                        clear_dialog
                        talk nasty talk "Fuck me. Chin up you pair of sad sacks."
                jump cave_woods_menu
            "[Pick up a branch] \\"Branch!\\" [Swing the branch about like it's a sword]":
                set data.cave.branch true
                talk nasty talk "Awooo!"
                talk lovely talk "Wheeee!"
                jump cave_woods_menu
            "[Look at a tree. Any tree]":
                set data.cave.tree true
                "Mushrooms. Fungus. It clings to the tree like a cancer. The tree is no longer just a tree, it is its own ecosystem."
                if (roll cave_woods_menu_fungus_orb orb 60):
                    choice:
                        talk orb talk "Fungus is from space. I just thought I should let you know."
                        "That's wild.":
                            talk orb talk "It is a bit. I'd keep your distance if I was you. I don't trust this stuff."
                        "Sheepshit. Nothing is from space. Space is fake.":
                            talk orb talk "Wow. Okay. I see how it is. Fine. Erase me. Whatever. I erased you first though, you vile and despicable woman."
                else:
                    wait 1000
                jump cave_woods_menu
            "[Become a little scrungler and run off into the woods to live as a feral animal]":
                set data.cave.scrungler true
                run transition scrungler
                choice:
                    "You scamper into the trees, squeaking, before tripping over a branch and landing on your stupid face."
                    "Okay done with that now. I like civilisation, having a cottage, running water etc.":
                        run skip
                run transition woods_one
                jump cave_woods_menu
            "[Be really quiet and listen to the birdsong]":
                set data.cave.song true
                stop music
                run transition woods_two
                "Your breathing quiets. The woods come to life."
                "The trees flock with birds, and each has its own song. You do not hear this in the city, nor on your lane, for the fields offer little comfort for birds."
                "The woods are different. In the woods you can hear them. They're beautiful. A tear forms in your eye."
                clear_dialog
                talk orb talk "I can understand them all... they're all so precious... so perfect..."
                clear_dialog
                play music ourlovelyladyverse
                talk nasty talk "TWEET TWEET TWEET! Bored. Let's go ass the holes."
                clear_dialog
                run transition woods_one
                jump cave_woods_menu
            "\\"PARSNIP! ARE YOU THERE!\\"":
                set data.cave.shout true
                "Your voice echoes through the trees, and eventually disappears into the breeze. There is no reply."
                jump cave_woods_menu
            roll cave_woods_menu_woods_orb orb 40 "Orb, tell me about the woods.":
                success "":
                    set data.cave.orb true
                    talk orb talk "The trees here are old. They have nested here longer than your species has lived, and they will long, long outlive you."
                    clear_dialog
                    choice:
                        talk orb talk "Your kind are leaves. You grow beautiful, then wither and fall when autumn comes."
                        "Wow damn I didn't ask you to neg me like that, Orb. Yikes :/":
                            talk orb talk "Sorry. Sorry."
                            if (roll cave_woods_menu_tree_orb orb 60):
                                talk orb talk "Actually, what I said wasn't even entirely true."
                                talk orb talk "These specific trees die in sixty-seven years. Replaced by an ugly private housing estate a twenty-minute drive away from the nearest shop. The dirt paths are drowned in tarmac and automobiles. Arteries clogged with lard."
                            else:
                                wait 1000
                    jump cave_woods_menu
                failure "":
                    set data.cave.orb true
                    choice:
                        talk orb talk "Trees."
                        "[Nod] Trees.":
                            jump cave_woods_menu

cave_cave:
    clear_dialog
    run transition cave
    choice:
        "The cave is considerably spookier up close. A signpost welded to the gate barring your entry reads thus: <span class='writtenText'>'NO ENTRY: DANGER TO LIFE AND LIMB'</span>."
        "Orb, do I have limbs? Should I be worried?":
            choice:
                talk orb talk "You have limbs, yes."
                "No. NO!":
                    talk orb talk "That's normal for rodents."
            if (roll cave_cave_life_nightmare nightmare 40):
                talk nightmare talk "<span class='nightmare'>a life on the other hand...</span>"
                clear_dialog
            talk lovely talk "Personally I'd rather not risk life *or* limb in the aid of a silly little sheep, but I suppose I'll just be ignored, as normal."
            talk nasty talk "Eh? Did someone talk? No? Must have been the wind..."
            choice:
                talk lovely talk "It was me! Don't ignore me on purpose! How cruel and evil! Squeak squeak!"
                "[Rattle the gate]":
                    play sound rattlegate
                    "The gate rattles."
        "[Rattle the gate]":
            play sound rattlegate
            "The gate rattles."
    clear_dialog
    talk nasty talk "Yup. That's a gate alright. Anyway, let's make like the NKVD finding the tsars hideout and bust this fucker down."
    talk lovely talk "W-what!? That's illegal! This is *council* property! Not to mention it's dangerous! Didn't you read the sign?"
    talk nasty talk "Read? I'd rather fucking eat my own shit."
    if (roll cave_cave_council_orb orb 60):
        talk orb talk "It isn't council property. You won't become a fugitive by breaking in. In fact the only criminal here is whoever wants us to think it isn't. It's not dangerous either, not really, if you don't wander too far..."
    else:
        wait 1000
    clear_dialog
    talk lovely talk "Goodness, I'm scared to go inside! It's dark, and slimy! There might be *creatures*!"
    talk nasty talk "So what? I have creatures crawling around in my hair already. What difference is a fucking... a fucking... a fucking centipedel going to make?"
    talk lovely talk "Scream!"
    clear_dialog
    jump cave_gate

cave_gate:
    clear_dialog
    choice:
        "The gate is no longer rattling, because you are not intentionally rattling it anymore."
        "[Inspect the gate]":
            "Some morning dew still clings to its bars. The chill from the cave seems to blow outwards. Your whiskers shiver."
            choice:
                "Your run your hand across the metal. Slightly rusted, it's rough to the touch. The fur on your hand is tinted bronze."
                "[Give your hand a lick]":
                    if (!= $data.ghost.hasTetnus true):
                        set data.ghost.hasTetnus true
                        run transition_disease
                        run diseaseCounter
                    "Tastes of tetnus."
                "[Don't give your hand a lick]":
                    run skip
            jump cave_gate
        roll cave_cave_rattle_nasty nasty 40 "[Attempt to break into the cave by rattling the gate so hard its hinges erode away into dust and it pops off of its frame]" if (!= (has_item? hammer) true):
            success "":
                play sound rattlegate
                wait 2000
                play sound metalcrash
                run transition_instant cave_noGate
                animate #narrat-app narrat-screenshake
                "The gate seems to come loose from its anchors, so violent is your rattling."
                clear_dialog
                talk nasty talk "Bloody hel, Ghost! Remind me never to get a handjob off of you! Cor!"
                jump cave_inside
            failure "":
                play sound rattlegate
                "You shake and shake and shake some more, but the gate remains stubbornly in place. Your arms hurt now."
                clear_dialog
                choice:
                    talk nasty talk "Gods. You're so fucking weedy, Ghost. It's embarrassing. Go on. Give it a kick."
                    roll cave_cave_kick_nasty nasty 80 "[Scream really loudly to power up and then kick the gate really hard]":
                        success "":
                            run transition_instant cave_noGate
                            animate #narrat-app narrat-screenshake
                            play sound metalcrash
                            "CLANG!"
                            clear_dialog
                            "The gate swings open. The padlock is flung into the cave and thuds against a rock. The glowing aura of power that has begun to surround you slowly fades away."
                            jump cave_inside
                        failure "":
                            play sound punch
                            run transition_pain
                            "You kick the gate, or at least you try to. You sort of swing your leg at it and scream, miss your mark, spin around several times and then crumple to the floor in a sad little heap."
                            talk nasty talk "Pathetic."
                            talk lovely talk "Goodness! Are you okay, Ghost?"
                            clear_dialog
                            choice:
                                talk orb talk "She's fine. Just a little dizzy."
                                "I'm going to kill myself.":
                                    choice:
                                        talk orb talk "No you aren't."
                                        "I don't think I'm going into that cave... sorry Parsnip... [Give up on your search] <span class='prompt'>[[CONTINUE]]</span>":
                                            play sound spendAction
                                            talk orb talk "I suppose there's not much point in us wandering around in the woods for any longer. If Parsnip where here we'd have found her by now. She'll have to find her own way home."
                                            complete_objective weapon parsnip
                                            complete_quest weapon weaponFailure
                                            stop ambient 1
                                            jump goToGameMap
        roll cave_cave_hammer_nasty nasty 20 "[Bash the lock off of the gate with your hammer]" if (has_item? hammer):
            success "":
                run transition_instant cave_noGate
                animate #narrat-app narrat-screenshake
                play sound metalcrash
                "CLANG!"
                clear_dialog
                choice:
                    "The gate swings open. The padlock is flung into the cave and thuds against a rock."
                    "\\"Wow!\\"":
                        jump cave_inside
                    "☑️ \\"Hammer time! 😎🤣\\" <span class='prompt'>[[END THE GAME IMMEDIATELY]]</span>":
                        jump ending_credits
            failure "":
                remove_item hammer 1
                play sound metalcrash
                "You strike the hammer against the gate, and the head shatters into tiny shards of metal. The lock remains undamaged."
                clear_dialog
                choice:
                    talk nasty talk "Fucking hel Ghost, you fucked that one."
                    "I think it was pretty cool how I made the hammer explode at least.":
                        jump cave_gate

cave_inside:
    clear_dialog
    talk lovely talk "Yipii! Oh Ghost, how strong you are! It's enough to make a lovely lady swoon!"
    choice:
        talk nasty talk "Hel yeah! Awooooooooooooooo!"
        "\\"Awoooooooooooo!\\" [Head into the cave, your 'awooing' echoing from the walls]":
            stop ambient 1
            play ambient amb_cave 2
            play sound footsteps
            run transition cave_inside
            clear_dialog
            choice:
                "The cave is dark, as they tend to be, but your 'spend too much time sleeping' eyes are quickly able to adjust to it. It is quiet, but not silent. Distantly there is water, and closer there is scuffling."
                "\\"HELLO!?\\"":
                    "Your voice echoes through the cave. The scuffling stops, for just a moment, and then continues."
                "Do any m- m- m- *monsters* live in here?":
                    talk orb talk "Any monsters? No. not really."
                    talk lovely talk "Do any... any creepy crawlies?"
                    if (roll cave_inside_spiders_orb orb 40):
                        set data.cave.crawlies true
                        talk orb talk "Not many, no. A few spiders, but that's all."
                        talk lovely talk "Oh me oh my! That's awfully scary! Still, one is glad the infestation is somewhat limited, at least!"
                        clear_dialog
                        wait 2000
                        talk lovely talk "Curious. I notice Nasty Girl isn't calling me a slur for 'coward'."
                        clear_dialog
                        wait 4000
                        choice:
                            talk lovely talk "Well well well well well well well! Nasty Girl is being uncharacteristically quiet, don't you think?"
                            "Nasty Girl are you there?":
                                choice:
                                    talk nasty talk "..."
                                    "Nasty Girl?":
                                        talk nasty talk "Fuck offfffff."
                    else:
                        talk orb talk "I guess we'll find out."
                "[Stoically march onwards, afraid of nothing]":
                    run skip
    clear_dialog
    choice:
        "Lime green moss clings to the cave walls. Oestromoss. It's like crawling through a furry intestine. A few pieces are missing, here and there..."
        "[Grab a bit of Oestromoss and eat it]":
            talk orb talk "It doesn't work like that. Sorry, Ghost."
        "[Leave it be]":
            run skip
    clear_dialog
    if (roll cave_inside_bite_orb orb 20):
        talk orb talk "Bite marks..."
        clear_dialog
    choice:
        "You turn a corner, and as you do, something drops from the ceiling, it lands on your head. A bit of pee comes out."
        "[Ignore it as hard as you can. Tense your brain really hard so you can get a comforting, distracting migraine]"
            "You feel a vein pop from the pressure you are exerting on your poor brain. The force seems to send whatever landed on you flying. You are once again alone."
        "[Brush *it* out of your hair]":
            run transition cave_spider
            set data.cave.crawlies true
            "You brush *it* out of your hair, and when you look at your hand, you look into the eyes of a little spider."
            clear_dialog
            choice:
                talk nasty talk "FUCK. FUCK. FUCK. KILL IT. FUCK. FUCK."
                "Hahaha! This bitch scared of bug! [Give the spider a little kiss and then shake it off of you]":
                    talk nasty talk "FUCK YOU. FUCK YOU. DIE. DIE."
                    talk lovely talk "Titter titter!"
                "It's okay Nasty Girl, I peed myself a little too. [Shake the spider off of you]":
                    talk nasty talk "...I- I didn't piss myself."
    clear_dialog
    choice:
        talk orb talk "Look, can we all just hold it together for a few more moments, okay. There's a corner up ahead, go around it, I sense something close, by which I mean the scuffling is mere meters away."
        "[Turn the corner]":
            play sound footsteps
            run transition cave_bunker
            clear_dialog
            "You turn the corner and are surprised by four things."
            "One: The cave has been turned into a makeshift storage and living space."
            "Two: The room is littered in plundered packets of <span class='writtenText'>'Genuine Survival Rations: Nutrient Powder. Nutrient content: 100%'</span>."
            "Four: Theres creature. She's covered in dust, with papery packaging tangled up in her wool. She looks like this is the best day of her life."
            clear_dialog
            talk lovely talk "Sheepy! Baa!"
    jump cave_bunker_menu

cave_bunker_menu:
    clear_dialog
    choice:
        "The strange, bunker and or sheep dining room sits before you. A shaft of light pierces through the ceiling, there is a route to the surface, but it has been covered by a grate."
        "[Look at the sheep]":
            talk orb talk "This is Parsnip."
            clear_dialog
            play sound baa
            choice:
                talk parsnip talk "Baa!"
                "\\"Baa!\\"":
                    "Parsnip vacantly blinks at you, before returning to her snack."
            clear_dialog
            talk orb talk "She must have found another way in. She was led here by the smell of the oestromoss, but when she arrived it was the other food that got the attention of her belly."
            clear_dialog
            choice:
                "Parsnip the sheep looks up at you. She looks *really* proud of her work."
                "[Pet her head] \\"Good sheep! What a hungry girl you are!\\"":
                    play sound baa
                    talk parsnip talk "Baaaa!"
                    clear_dialog
                    "Parsnip licks your hand, and then returns to snacking on some <span class='writtenText'>'nutrient powder'</span>."
                "[Don't encourage her]":
                    "Parsnip returns to snacking on some <span class='writtenText'>'nutrient powder'</span>."
            jump cave_bunker_menu
        "[Look around the room]":
            "Someone planned, or plans to live here for a long *long* time. It wouldn't be comfortable, nor would it actually work long term. It's the aesthetics of a survival bunker, not an actual survival bunker. A hidden room to make someone feel less scared. A nightlight. A comfort blankie. A drunkard's flask."
            if (roll cave_bunker_menu_bunker_orb orb 80):
                set data.cave.orbKnows true
                talk orb talk "The Weapon. They built this place for the end. For after the end."
            else:
                wait 1000
            jump cave_bunker_menu
        "[Pick up a packet of <span class='writtenText'>'Genuine Survival Rations: Nutrient Powder. Nutrient content: 100%'</span>]":
            "The packet has been chewed open. A grim mixture of dusty beige powder and sheep saliva clings to it, but it has for the most part been devoured."
            if (roll cave_bunker_menu_nutrient_orb orb 60):
                talk orb talk "This is powdered milk mixed with flour, crab chitin, sawdust and asbestos. It has about as much nutritional value as eating cobalt-60. Or paper. It varies from packet to packet."
                talk nasty talk "Yum! Love me some paper."
                talk lovely talk "Indeed! When Papi fed me some of his tax returns it was rather yummy! I wish I had been able to savour it, but he was ever so insistent that I finish my meal before the tax officer visited!"
                clear_dialog
            choice:
                "A bit of the 'nutrient powder' sticks to your finger. It feels like cornflour (bad and evil)."
                "[Take a lick]":
                    run diseaseCounter
                    run transition_disease
                    "It tastes of sheep saliva, sheep flu and asbestosis."
                "[Don't take a lick, even though you really want to]":
                    talk nasty talk "Such restraint... you're a real fucking nun, Ghost."
            jump cave_bunker_menu
        "<span class='prompt'>[[MOVE ON]]</span>" if $data.cave.crawlies:
            talk nasty talk "Can we get a fucking move on. This cave sucks big shits and it's full of... fucking... crawlies. Fuck you."
            jump cave_leave
        "<span class='prompt'>[[MOVE ON]]</span>" if (!= $data.cave.crawlies true):
            talk nasty talk "Can we get a fucking move on. This cave sucks big shits and I'm bored."
            jump cave_leave

cave_leave:
    choice:
        talk lovely talk "Quite, I think it's high time we head home victorious!"
        "\\"Pspspspspspsps!\\" [Do the 'pspspsps' hand gesture at Parsnip] \\"Come on Parsnip!\\" [Pick a clump of oestromoss off of the wall and use it to lure her home]":
            play sound baa 3
            talk parsnip talk "Baa!"
            clear_dialog
            "Parsnip follows you eagerly, distracted from the huge amount of oestromoss available inside the cave by the small clump you've taken with you."
    clear_dialog
    choice:
        talk nasty talk "Fuck me lads. Looks like we've succeeded at our quest. Fucking ace."
        "\\"Fucking ace! Awooo!\\" [Head back to The Weapon with a great big smug look on your face]":
            stop sound 2
            stop ambient 2
            clear_dialog
            play sound footsteps
            run transition woods_two
            wait 4000
            play sound footsteps
            run transition fields
            clear_dialog
            "The Weapon's chewing straw drops out of their agape mouth as they see you approach, Parsnip at your side."
            if (roll cave_bunker_menu_lovely lovely 20):
                talk lovely talk "It's been a while. They had started to doubt you would actually come through."
            else:
                wait 1000
            clear_dialog
            choice:
                talk weapon talk "You... you found her?"
                "\\"I did! She was in a cave eating oestromoss and something called <span class='writtenText'>'nutrient powder!'</span>. What a charmed life!\\"" if (!= $data.cave.orbKnows true):
                    talk parsnip talk "Baa!"
                "\\"She was in your cave eating oestromoss and something called <span class='writtenText'>'nutrient powder!'</span>. What a charmed life!\\"" if $data.cave.orbKnows:
                    talk parsnip talk "Baa!"
                "\\"You doubted me?\\" [Make big pleading eyes nobody could possibly admit to doubting]":
                    choice:
                        talk weapon talk "Yes. Where was she?"
                        "\\"She was in a cave eating oestromoss and something called <span class='writtenText'>'nutrient powder!'</span>. What a charmed life!\\"" if (!= $data.cave.orbKnows true):
                            play sound baa
                            talk parsnip talk "Baa!"
                        "\\"She was in your cave eating oestromoss and something called <span class='writtenText'>'nutrient powder!'</span>. What a charmed life!\\"" if $data.cave.orbKnows:
                            play sound baa
                            talk parsnip talk "Baa!"
            clear_dialog
            if $data.cave.orbKnows:
                talk weapon talk "M- my cave?"
                clear_dialog
                "They squint. There's something behind your vacant little eyes. A smidge of smug, otherworldly colour."
                clear_dialog
                if $data.interview.orbKnows:
                    talk weapon talk "Again you are full of surprises, little rat... smarter than you let on..."
                else:
                    talk weapon talk "You're smarter than you look, little Rat."
                clear_dialog
                "They sigh."
                clear_dialog
            talk weapon talk "Attracted to the Oestromoss in my bunker... Mmm... I was thinking of scraping it all off of the walls and throwing it away, you know? Don't want that stuff near me, but I stayed my hand..."
            choice:
                talk weapon talk "There are folks who might need it, you know? After the end, if anyone other than me makes it..."
                "\\"Sorry, did you just say <span class='writtenText'>'in my bunker'</span>? That was *your* cave?\\"" if (!= $data.cave.orbKnows true):
                    run skip
                "\\"Are you not going to elaborate on the bunker?\\"" if $data.cave.orbKnows:
                    run skip
            "A brief silence. The Weapon is visibly irritated with themself for giving you this in. They sigh."
            clear_dialog
            talk weapon talk "Aye... 'tis. Nothing untoward about having a bunker, little lady... we should all be prepared..."
            clear_dialog
            if (== $data.weapon.finderFee 0):
                choice:
                    talk weapon talk "Well. That's that sorted then... we agreed on this being... what, communist direct action? So I owe you nothing except my thanks. Well then. Thank you, Ghost."
                    "\\"No problem, comrade.\\" [Do a gay little salute at your comrade]":
                        choice:
                            talk weapon talk "Mhm... anyway, I should be paying more attention to the flock, just in case radical thought has started to spread through them as it did Parsnip... and yourself."
                            "\\"Okay! I'll take my radical thoughts elsewhere!\\" [Do a gay little wave and leave] <span class='prompt'>[[CONTINUE]]</span>":
                                play sound spendAction
                                talk weapon talk "Mhm."
                                jump goToGameMap
                clear_dialog
            else:
                "They rifle though their pocket and pull out some coins."
                if (== $data.weapon.redHanded true):
                    add_stat money 5
                    play sound coins
                elseif (== $data.weapon.finderFee 35):
                    add_stat money 35
                    play sound coins
                elseif (== $data.weapon.finderFee 20):
                    add_stat money 20
                    play sound coins
                else:
                    add_stat money 5
                    play sound coins
                clear_dialog
                if (== $data.weapon.redHanded true):
                    choice:
                        talk weapon talk "For your trouble. I'd give you more if you hadn't tried to rob me. Let that be a lesson to you, eh?"
                        "\\"Yipiii! I can buy one, maybe two sweeties now! Thank you!\\"":
                            talk weapon talk "Mhm."
                else:
                    choice:
                        talk weapon talk "For your trouble."
                        "\\"Yipiii! I can buy so many sweeties now! Thank you!\\"":
                            talk weapon talk "Mhm."
                complete_objective weapon parsnip
                complete_quest weapon weaponSuccess
                clear_dialog
                if $data.weapon.redHanded:
                    "The Weapon walks off without so much as a 'Mhm, well, goodbye'."
                    if (roll cave_leave_bye_lovely lovely 40):
                        talk lovely talk "They're still pretty angry about that plank, I'm afraid."
                    choice:
                        talk orb talk "I'm not convinced all that trouble was worth the pennies, to be honest."
                        "Going outside is *always* worth it, Orb. <span class='prompt'>[[CONTINUE]]</span>":
                            play sound spendAction
                            jump goToGameMap
                else:
                    "The wind whistles. This conversation should be over. The Weapon should be telling you to clear off... but they don't."
                    "The Weapon glowers at you."
                    if (roll cave_bunker_menu_glower_lovely lovely 40):
                        talk lovely talk "It's a good glower, in a sense. They don't hate you, so much as they really, *really* hate that they've gotten to quite like you."
                    else:
                        wait 1000
                    clear_dialog
                    talk weapon talk "Tell me... would... would you like to come inside and... have a cup of tea?"
                    if (roll cave_bunker_menu_tea_lovely lovely 60):
                        talk lovely talk "They have not socialised in a long, long time. They never really did, to be honest."
                    else:
                        wait 1000
                    clear_dialog
                    play sound baa
                    talk parsnip talk "Baa!"
                    clear_dialog
                    talk weapon talk "Not you. Back in the field. Go on, off with you, troublemaker."
                    clear_dialog
                    "Parsnip toddles away into the field and is welcomed back to the flock by a chorus of 'baas'. The Weapon turns back to you."
                    clear_dialog
                    choice:
                        talk weapon talk "Well?"
                        "\\"Mmm I love tea! Yes please!\\" <span class='prompt'>[[-1 ACTION]]</span>" if (>= $stats.actions.value 1):
                            play sound spendAction
                            talk weapon talk "Mmm. Okay then. Only quick mind, these sheep aren't going to watch themselves."
                            jump boardgame
                        "\\"Mmm I love tea! But unfortunately due to circumstances and events, I am out of actions for the day, so I must turn you down.\\"" if (<= $stats.actions.value 0):
                            choice:
                                talk weapon talk "I see... well, if you insist. Still, thank you for your help."
